<TITLE> DU convocation on Dec 12 to be 'largest ever' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 10 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka University's 45th convocation on Dec 12 will be the biggest in the university's history, vice-chancellor AAMS Arefin Siddique said on Thursday. "Some 4203 graduates, 1328 post graduates, 58 M Phil holders, 58 doctorates and 3411 others will be attending the convocation. Around 3,500 guests will also be present at the ceremony," he told a press conference. Yuan T Lee, who won the Nobel Chemistry Prize in 1986, has been invited to be the convocation speaker. The university will confer an honorary Doctor of Science degree on Lee. Former DU student in chemistry Abul Hussam, inventor of the 'Sono' arsenic filter will also be awarded an honorary Doctor of Science degree, and historian Ranajit Guha a Doctor of Literature degree. The first convocation of the university following its establishment was on Feb 22 1923. Three convocations have been held since Bangladesh's independence in 1999, 2000 and 2004. bdnew
